M|copy-editing|**Symptom:** List of what the product does without why it matters
M|copy-editing|**Fix:** Add "which means..." after each feature to bridge to benefits
M|copy-editing|**Symptom:** "Leverage synergies to optimize outcomes"
M|copy-editing|**Fix:** Ask "How would a human say this?" and use those words
M|copy-editing|**Symptom:** Starting with company history or vague statements
M|copy-editing|**Fix:** Lead with the reader's problem or desired outcome
M|copy-editing|**Symptom:** The ask comes after too much buildup, or isn't clear
M|copy-editing|**Fix:** Make the CTA obvious, early, and repeated
M|copy-editing|**Symptom:** "Customers love us" with no evidence
M|copy-editing|**Fix:** Add specific testimonials, numbers, or case references
M|copy-editing|**Symptom:** "We help businesses grow"
M|copy-editing|**Fix:** Specify who, how, and by how much
M|copy-editing|**Symptom:** Copy tries to speak to everyone, resonates with no one
M|copy-editing|**Fix:** Pick one audience and write directly to them
M|copy-editing|**Symptom:** Listing every capability, overwhelming the reader
M|copy-editing|**Fix:** Focus on 3-5 key benefits that matter most to the audience
M|copy-editing|When editing collaboratively:
M|copy-editing|1. **Run a sweep and present findings** - Show what you found, why it's an issue
M|copy-editing|2. **Recommend specific edits** - Don't just identify problems; propose solutions
M|copy-editing|3. **Request the updated copy** - Let the author make final decisions
M|copy-editing|4. **Verify previous sweeps** - After each round of edits, re-check earlier sweeps
M|copy-editing|5. **Repeat until clean** - Continue until a full sweep finds no new issues
M|copy-editing|This iterative process ensures each edit doesn't create new problems while respecting the author's ownership of the copy.
